!iflang [english]

!begin_node Cookie, OPMM

(!B)Open Helper(!b)

The program assists at a 'Fopen' call when the path is incorrect.
On demand an attempt is made to convert '/' to '\' (UNIX-mode) and 
a path-name table is used. In addition the pathname can be output 
to the printer/screen/MIDI port.

Modifies the (!nolink [GEMDOS]) vector and for (!nolink [TOS]) <1.06 the
reset vector.

Status: PD

!end_node

